          <h3>Technical</h3>
          <p>The projector is a full HD 1080P projector with a 1920x1080 resolution. On stage there will be HDMI and mini-DP cables to connect to the projector. If your laptop needs a special adapter to connect to HDMI, please bring one.</p>
          
          <p>If your presentation requires sound, please let us know before the conference starts so a cable to connect to the PA can be provided for you.</p>

          <p>On stage there is also a dedicated WIFI ap for speakers. The network is called <strong>ColdFront16 Speakers</strong> and the password is <strong>10gerdyr</strong>. This connection can be used if you need a connection to Internet for your talk, but please keep in mind that it's powered by 4G.</p>

          <h3>Your talk</h3>

          <p>Please make yourself familiar with the schedule and the time for your talk. Please be by the stage about 15 minutes before it is your turn to enter the stage. There is a longer break after every second talk. Your speaker slot is <strong>45 minutes</strong>, and it's up to you if you wanna have an Q/A. We got mic's available if needed</p>

          <p>We also encourage you to put your slides online after your talk.</p>          
          
          <h3>Filming and streaming</h3>
          <p>Your talk will be professionally filmed and published on our <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCZHbZVjG2wXaLCuHK3LZ5lw">YouTube channel</a> as fast as possible after the conference. All videos published will be published under a CC BY-NC-SA 3.0 licence.</p>

          <p>If you do not want your talk to be filmed, published or streamed, please let us know up front.</p>

